FBIS3-20185 "drweu060_h_94009" FBIS-WEU-94-060 Document Type:Daily Report 29 Mar 1994 GERMANY Siemens Starts Joint Venture With Chinese Firm AU2903130994 Paris AFP in English 1256 GMT 29 Mar 94 AU2903130994 Paris AFP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Erlangen, Germany, March 29 (AFP) -- German industrial group Siemens has set up a joint venture with Chinese firm Machine Tool Electric Appliance Factory (SMTEAF) in Suzhou, eastern China, the German group announced on Tuesday. It said the joint venture, to employ 1,400 people in an initial phase, would make low-voltage electricity distribution equipment. Investments will amount to 100 million marks over five years, the announcement said. Siemens will hold a majority stake in the company, to be called Siemens Electrical Apparatus Ltd. Siemens senior executive Carl-Heiner Thomas said the purpose of the joint venture is to commercialize Siemens technology on the Chinese market and acquire a larger presence on Southern Asian markets.
